    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What is the difference between the Alfa Laval MAB and MOPX centrifuge series?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The Alfa Laval MAB series are solid-retaining (manual-clean) <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/" class="text-navy underline hover:text-gold">disc-stack centrifuges</a>, meaning accumulated solids must be manually removed by stopping the centrifuge. The <a href="/alfa-laval-mopx-207-centrifuge/" class="text-navy underline hover:text-gold">MOPX series</a> are self-cleaning centrifuges that automatically eject separated solids during operation without stopping. MAB centrifuges are simpler and more economical for applications with lower solids loading.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What fluids can an Alfa Laval MAB centrifuge process?</summary>
