    </details>
    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">How often does an Alfa Laval MAB centrifuge need to be cleaned?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Cleaning frequency depends on the solids loading of the process fluid. For relatively clean fluids like turbine lube oil, cleaning intervals may be several days. For dirtier fluids with higher particulate content, the bowl may need manual cleaning every few hours. The sludge space capacity of each model (ranging from 0.40 gallons on the MAB 204 to 2.00 gallons on the MAB 209) also affects cleaning intervals.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Does Dolphin Centrifuge supply Alfa Laval MAB centrifuge parts?</summary>
